\section{Pattern DTO}

Le pattern DTO (\textit{Data Transfer Object}) découple la structure de la base de données du contrat de l'API.

\begin{center}
\begin{tikzpicture}[node distance=0.8cm,
  box/.style={rectangle, rounded corners=4pt, draw=accentblue, fill=lightgray,
              minimum width=4.5cm, minimum height=1cm, align=center, font=\small},
  step/.style={rectangle, rounded corners=4pt, draw=borderblue, fill=white,
               minimum width=5cm, align=left, font=\small, inner sep=6pt}
]

  \node[box, fill=accentblue!15] (req) {\textbf{Request DTO}\\\small Corps JSON + validation \texttt{@Valid}};
  \node[step, below=0.4cm of req] (s1) {
    \textbf{Contrôleur :} Lit les IDs du DTO\\
    $\rightarrow$ \texttt{findById(id)} pour chaque relation\\
    $\rightarrow$ Lance \texttt{404} si introuvable
  };
  \node[box, below=0.4cm of s1, fill=darkblue!10] (ent) {\textbf{Entité JPA}\\\small Objet Hibernate avec relations \texttt{@ManyToOne}};
  \node[step, below=0.4cm of ent] (s2) {
    \textbf{Conversion statique :}\\
    \texttt{MissionResponse.convert(mission)}\\
    Extrait les noms, exclut le mot de passe
  };
  \node[box, below=0.4cm of s2, fill=publichint!15] (resp) {\textbf{Response DTO}\\\small JSON plat envoyé au client};

  \draw[arrow] (req.south) -- (s1.north);
  \draw[arrow] (s1.south) -- (ent.north);
  \draw[arrow] (ent.south) -- (s2.north);
  \draw[arrow] (s2.south) -- (resp.north);

\end{tikzpicture}
\end{center}

